She answered that the vehicle belonged to another tenant who was looking for it. I was always there. I was really confused with her answer. I told her that I was not going to look for Nobody at nine o'clock at night was not my job and I have been in another rented place and this one in specific and it is nothing personal but there is no good service or professionalism, the company should take attention and correct the bad service of this cubesmart Storage. .

< Review>
Keep in mind that this Starbucks is operated by Target and not Starbucks, so the issues are with Target, not Starbucks. This location is inside the store, so you must walk in. They are always short staffed, so it takes forever to get your order. There has been numerous times when there was only one person there, you place an order, that person makes it, then they help the next customer. If there is more than two or three people in line forget it. The food selection is okay, but they lack many items due to the small size of the location. I go there if I have the extra time and shipping at Target, but there is not my goto location. On the bright side, the staff is amazing, never got an order wrong, and are always friendly. That alone is the only reason I'm willing to go here.</Review>

<rate>4<//rate>< Review>
We knew in advance there would be a bit of a wait (around 40 min) Seems standard for this location.  No reservations accepted. We were seated in the patio area. The indoor seating was also available. The overall ambiance is relaxed. It was a Sat. morning (11am) and there were families as well as couples and small groups. The drink menu offers specialty drinks from giant mimosa and baby Moscow mules(serve 2-4 people) to specialty lemonades and coffees.  The menu offered something for everyone - Breakfast, lunch and appetizers with a heavy focus on breakfast type dishes. Vegan dishes were available as well as a kids.  The menu was quite diverse Breakfast skillets, crepes, tamale plates, burgers, sandwiches and salads. The average price for a dish is about 17.00 but the portions are good sized. The restroom was clean and well stocked.  The service was fast and friendly without being overbearing.<//Review>

The service was very good.  The place was half full and pleasantly quiet.  I‚Äôd recommend giving it a try.  I plan to go back next time I‚Äôm in the area.<//Text><Rating>4</Rating></record>

< Review>
This was one of the best omelettes that I've had. I worked as a breakfast chef for four years in a 4 star restaurant which means that I tend to be a bit critical of an omelette and they really did it justice. The egg was cooked perfectly and each ingredient complemented the next. There was just the right amount of cheese and the ratio on each ingredient was spot on. As a chef you understand that an omelette can be a very difficult task to perfect and the chef that made mine has it figured out!
I will definitely be back to try more of the menu!<//Review>

114732676675772659761< /userid>
<username>Craig Beck</username><date>1582645165261< /date><rating>2<//rating><Text>After learning about this place via the news, I was excited to try this place with a close friend who is an Egg's Benedict connoisseur of sorts.  When we finally got a chance to go (there were 4 of us), we were extremely disappointed.  Admittedly, give the number of high reviews, this could have just been a bad day for the chef, but we won't be going back.

Out of the 4 of us, 3 ordered a benedict menu item.  While two of us are traditionalists and enjoy a perfectly runny yoke, one likes theirs cooked to about medium (solid, but with a little ooze).  When we received our orders, all three eggs were hard-hard boiled (completely solid yoke).  We had to send two plates back to get proper poached eggs, while the third just ate it despite being dissatisfied.  When the plates were returned one had decently poached while the other was nearly completely raw (shouldn't have runny whites of the egg).

I had the Border Benedict, which comes with an english muffin, tomato slice, chorizo, avocado, salsa and the poached egg.  Unfortunately, my entire plate was completely saturated in salsa "juice".  The muffins were just soggy former relics and the country potatoes were bathing in water.

Another had the Irish Benedict which had Corned Beef for the meat.  The meat was perfectly on point (I even tried it), however, he had the nearly raw egg and the hollandaise was plain awful.  It was clear they use some sort of powdered hollandaise or perhaps powdered eggs to make it - very disappointing.

While the food was a completely let down, I will say the wait staff was great, the restaurant was clean and inviting, plus the drinks were good.  Had the food been on point, this place would easily get 5 starts.  Sadly, despite purporting itself as specializing in benedicts, our experience was a complete letdown.  Two stars as the wait staff was good and the interior was pleasant, food unfortunately brings down the rating.</Text>< pics>

< text>
Unless you're looking to get tanked on cheap bubbles, there's no reason to go here.

There is no ambiance.  You're basically sitting in plain, square cafeteria style room.  It's loud, and on top of that, on our visit they were playing country music way too loud, which forces everyone to talk even louder.

Service was non existent.  We sat at the bar, but the half dozen bartenders were too busy slinging drinks to pay us any mind.

It took over an hour to get our food.  One order was cold, the hollandaise had solidified into a weirdly gelatinous texture.  The other order was okay, but nothing worth returning for.

If you want to be surrounded by loud annoying drunk people, mediocre food and bad service, just go to any dive bar and you'll do better.< /text>

< Text>
Went to the Friends with Benedicts Mimosa House for the first time on New Years Eve morning.  Had a great experience with a highly efficient waiter and terrific food.  As some have noted the food doesn't just come out a minute after one has placed an order and there is a reason for that.  Unlike, other places they actually cook the food as it is ordered.  Not ahead of time like way to many places do and it keep it warming.  I prefer to have fresh cooked food and if I have to  wait a little longer so be it. I want fresh..  Maybe I'm old fashioned but to me the restaurant experience was great from A to Z.<//Text>

<Pictures>None</Pictures><Time>1526431417377<//Time>< Text>
I had the worst experience here on Sunday (Mothers Day). I have been dying to eat here, so my husband took my mom and I here on Mothers Day.  I tried so hard to give them the benefit of the doubt because it was busy.  So this review will not talk about the wait time or how crowded it was or anything like that. I can forgive that, however I can not forgive the rest of the experience.
Once we finally got our food the waitress was in such a hurry to pass out the plates, that she neglected to tell my husband that his skillet was hot! So he grabbed it and burned his thumb. He immediately put his thumb into his ice water for relief.  The waitress said nothing! So I went up to the hostess, because all of the wait staff were busy.  I went to her to ask if we could get some ice in a bag or something of that effect for his finger.  Right next to the hostess was a man and he just ignored the whole convo, but heard it and acknowledged that I was there. Within minutes his finger was blistered and still burning. Our waiter brought out the ice with a packet of ointment for a burn and asked my husband to please put it on his thumb. Time went by and no one came out to talk to us or even ask if he was okay.  I was shocked! I would have thought that at least the manager would have come and said something! ANYTHING!!! So I asked the waiter when we were leaving if the man at the front with the hostess was the manager and he said no, he was the owner!!! I was shocked..
Secondly I ordered one of the benedicts the food was cold and the English muffin was so hard that I could barley cut it with a knife, let alone my teeth.
Needless to say, I am sad. I wanted to like this place and like I said I let a lot of stuff go that day, that I am not even writing about because they were so busy with Mothers day, but this I can't see past! I am so disappointed!< /Text>

< review>
The food was wonderful, sadly the service was not.  15 minutes after being seated with no one having come by to check on us or take our order, my husband was ready to leave. I was hungry and I really wanted to try the place so I recommended we wait another 3-5 minutes. About 5 minutes later our waiter finally came by, this was a Thursday morning and the place was not busy. No apology for the delay.

I ordered the sailor benedict, but asked first how long it would take as I was hungry, and a waterfall mimosa. The mimosa was ok, the benedict, with crab, salmon and shrimp was delicious. My husband had the linguica scramble (?) which he said was very good. I might be willing to give it another try although with so many good breakfast choices around probably not. I definitely would not go on a weekend, if service is bad when it‚Äôs slow it must be terrible on the weekends when I‚Äôve heard the place is crazy busy.</review>

<rate>5<//rate>< review>
I'm writing this on May 15th, 2021, and the current COVID-safe setup they have with reserving a lane for family swim or lap swim or reserving a time slot in a class works very well and feels very safe! Each time slot gives you 45 minutes of time in the pool, with 15 minutes in between so it never feels crowded and there's time for them to clean surfaces between groups. The pool and facility are very clean and while the water is a tad chilly if you're just standing still, it's actually plenty warm once you get swimming.<//review>

< Text>
I love swimming at this pool. Great programs for beginner lessons, swim teams for adults and kids as well as open swim on the weekends. The pool is clean and clear. They keep the water pretty warm all year round. Staff is helpful and skillful.< /Text>

< Name>
Brian Gillespie< /Name>
< review>
Great outdoor pool! Well kept and friendly staff. I go to this pool for lap swimming about twice a week and is so much better than gym pools. The best times is when lap swimming is opened up to 50m! They use a sodium based chlorine that cuts down on the over chlorinated feeling. At the time of writing, open during Covid, and kept safe and managed well.</review>

< username>
Jordan Charter</username>
< Time>
1595275419488< /Time>
< Rate>
4</Rate>
< Review>
I typically swim at a city swim complex near USC, but it remains closed due to COVID-19. I have wanted to try the Culver City Plunge for years, but it always seemed too busy for my liking. I am a decent swimmer, but definitely not a *confident* one so I prefer having a lane to myself. Now that the plunge has reopened and they only allow one person per lane I figured it was a great time to try it out. Firstly I am quite impressed with the measures they are taking to ensure the safety of patrons. It's well-organized and well-executed. I docked one star because there has been more than on occasion in which one of the staff members checking us in has had his mask over his mouth, but not his nose. It defeats the purpose of wearing a mask if you have your nose exposed. A few patrons in line are sometimes guilty of this as well which is somewhat vexing. All that said, the pool is lovely and the staff is as well. Overall, a great place to come for a swim.< /Review>

<user_name>Steve Hoover<//user_name><Resp>None<//Resp>< review>
We had our first office visit our our little dog Rasty.  First impression?  The place was spotless and utterly immaculate...we were greeted by two gracious and efficient persons at the counter (I regret the I failed to get their names).

We were escorted to an examination room, also spotless, and greeted by a very kind and pleasant vet tech, Jovani (sp) who efficiently filled out paperwork and prepared our pet for the examination to follow.

Within minutes, Dr. Chen appeared and gave Rasty a thorough checkup and her required vaccine booster shot.  He also was the epitome of caring professionalism, and our crazy little dog responded to him with affection...a true test, eh?

We are delighted with the care, the cleanliness, and the compassion of the entire team...our gratitude is boundless...We feel very fortunate to have found them.</review>

1419434776384</date>
<Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
Last week, our Black Lab of almost 13 years old was in really bad shape. I tried to call her regular veterinarian, but he wouldn't be in in that afternoon. I searched the web and read some reviews and called El Camino Veterinary Hospital, made the appointment for 2 hours later. The front desk person was really nice and explained all the options and prices for us. The veterinarian made a examination and explain all our questions in a very sincere way. Since we didn't want our dog to suffer anymore, we made the option for euthanasia. : (  He also told us that we could say our goodbyes to our sweet Lucy and after the process was done we could stay a little longer in the room with her. The place is clean, the staff is really nice and very accommodating and yesterday we receive a "Thinking of You" card from the staff of El Camino Vet. Hospital. I thought that it was a good reason besides the well care that was given to Lucy to write a review. Thank you very much for your kindness.</Review>

<user_name>Ulia M.< /user_name>< pictures>
None</pictures>
<Text>This hospital has a very welcoming staff, they are always polite and helpful. I can always call them and ask a question whenever I have any concerns without actually coming in.
Dr. Morgan is very experienced and he has on many occasions saved me money because I happen to be an overreacting person. He recommends the necessary treatment without pushing the extra expenses by telling me about the options I can do myself at home.
I also happened to get Dr. Perry once, who listened to my rambling with no complaints, was very caring and professional. Dr. Perry also had helpful suggestion for dental care, which is never an issue until it's too late, so the advice was definitely a big plus.
The vet techs are supportive, enjoy the company of your pet and love what they do, they always handle my cats with love and care. People tend to overlook the techs but trust me they do a lot of work and spend the most time with your pets!
My cats have been here for over a year and so far so good! I've asked a ton of questions every time I came in about shots, type/brand of food, litter, deworming, spaying etc. I've also visited them when they used to do emergency visits, back in the day.
I'm not going to lie, there are cheaper vet offices out there, but really not by that much. They also offer a free follow up appointment, which is definitely worth mentioning. You can schedule an appointment for free up to 10 days or so later as long as it is for the same issue, to re-examine and check the progress.< /Text><Time>1446254870949</Time></record></dataset><record>

< text>
Went here in Jan 2020 to get my dog's annual shots of taken care of. She is very friendly with people and she shrank into me and my spouse as soon as the Dr. came in dressed in extra protective arm and hand gear and stated she had experience with aggressive dogs and was clearly acting nervous despite her copious explanations of experience. We were both taken aback at this comment and asked why she assumed our Staffordshire Terrier was aggressive.  She could not give us an answer. Our dog became more and more nervous as she explained they'd need to concoct a substitute for one of the shots since it was not in stock and it would be administered to the mouth via a needleless shot. We explained our dog became frightened when foreign objects were brought near her face. We tried to help administer the drug (laying on the floor at one point) with no success until finally one of the assistants suggested putting it with food which worked well. This of course was after our dog was traumatized (and only worked after the Dr. left the room). We will not be returning.</text>

< Text>
This is the first time I have ever taken a pet of mine to a Vet. I didn't know what to expect but I'm so glad I found this place. I was a bit late to my appointment but they seen my pet almost as soon as we got there. The staff was extremely friendly, knowledgeable and inviting. <user_id>115975364144658975355<//user_id><name>River Faille<//name><time>1342126596525</time>< Rating>
2</Rating>
< Review>
The emergency vet Dr. Chen failed to notice a mass in my 2 year old cat's abdomen when I brought him in due to lack of appetite, and prescribed my cat suffering from a liver failure antibiotics for a mouth infection (which I suspected was the cause but I took him to a veterinarian because I am not one.) He essentially prescribed my cat poison that killed him. Granted he was 2 and not obese, so lipidosis was a fluke. I did express concern over his lethargy and failure to eat as well as vomiting and called when he continued to vomit, they said his appetite should come back after the antibiotics and I trusted them. Having a feeling that El Camino may not be a very good vet, I took him to Midtown animal hospital a few days later (as soon as I could get an appointment) when the antibiotics were making him vomit worse. Midtown noticed a massive liver immediately and then confirmed this on an X-ray then referred me to VCA referral emergency hospital in Rancho Cordova, because they don't do intensive care there, and told me about CARE credit because their services are very expensive (but worth it.) So I am struggling to get my cat seen by the real emergency veterinary service now to find out if it is in any way treatable. My cat is now yellow with jaundice and in hospital. Meanwhile, it is force feeding to keep him from going downhill too painfully and pain meds and many costly diagnostics. Don't waste your money here on subpar veterinary services - go somewhere that the vets are not negligent and just trying to sell you something that may or may not help then get you out the door instead of this horrible place. Dr. Chen is negligent and does not care about your pet.

Update: My beloved cat died, $5000 in debt later of what would have been a very treatable disease if caught earlier by a competent vet. I wasted $150 on incompetent diagnosis and would consider suing them in small claims court if I were not moving out of state next week. They did not offer to reimburse me for their misdiagnosis and negligence. They are the one vet that did not send a sympathy card of the 3 we went to in this ordeal too. Not that any amount of money can ever replace my Vlad cat. I cry myself to sleep at night and kick myself every day for going there because it had good reviews, was close and was the only emergency vet I knew about at the time. We lost precious days that might have made a difference by being steered wrong here and believing that he "would be fine after antibiotics." and that the throwing up was "no big deal" and would soon stop. That would probably work most of the time, but if you are a veterinarian, you should rule out anything catastrophic with a simple blood test and not prescribe an antibiotic with a side effect of nausea without anti-emetics and appetite stimulants to a cat that won't eat, from what other vets I took my cat to subsequently when trying to save him have said. Of course I wanted to believe that he didn't need any of that. That cat meant a lot to me, and laid by my side every day when I was recovering from a miscarriage and found out I can never have children. Don't lose your beloved pet by trusting incompetent vets who do not know what to feel for in the abdomen and tell you 'blood tests aren't necessary' when your pet is sick. Of course you want to believe that your pet is okay and to trust a vet, but I'd rather pay for real diagnostics than go somewhere that will guess and lie, pretending to know what they are doing. Go to a real emergency vet! (VCA or Davis.) I will definitely be filing a complaint.</Review>

It's a warm and intimate location that has all the trappings of a great spa that I enjoy. Cozy waiting room with a fireplace, attentive front-desk staff, snacks/water and amazing therapists. We thought it was perfect for us.

My wife and I enjoyed a massage from Victor and Vivian, which my wife said her's was "life changing". I had Victor for mine and he did some moves I had never even experienced before. He did this thing with my neck/skull area that made my body go limp. I even tried to have my wife do it at home the next day.

My favorite part was the facial with Liz. As a guy, I have very little experience with facials and she immediately made me feel comfortable and was able to get me to open up and explain what I wanted out of the treatment. I told Liz I wanted to relax and "make my skin look fresh". We decided on the Vitamin C facial for me and I laid down and she went to do her thing. The whole process was enjoyable and she even did this amazing arm massage that was perfect. I left completely relaxed and my wife said my face was glowing.

I live in the general area and I'll be coming back whenever I need to unwind.</text>

Good food alhamdulillah, side note: Speaking of other restaurants, sometimes I lose respect for Halal places when I see them giving into selling alcohol or have music blasting.. or even inappropriate things on TV playing. I've experienced this many times at many different halal food* restaurants. Alhamdulillah none of that was the case with this restaurant. It was pleasant to hear Qur'an being played from a distance of 10ft from the restaurant door. The owner was friendly, said Salaam and gave good service. Much respect. The chicken in the sandwich was also good alhamdulillah. I felt the pricing was a little bit expensive, but maybe that's just how it is with getting halal chicken and all. I haven't been to that many fried chicken places to know competitive pricing.</text>

Severely over priced</Text>

<pics>None<//pics><user_id>103285552387339363599<//user_id><rating>1<//rating><GmapID>0x80c2d908d8426e4f:0x73be050fc7c64ee0</GmapID><date>1610832037070</date></record></dataset><record>
<user_id>114719352306972897517< /user_id><user_name>Ken Bro< /user_name>< date>
1563220034727<//date>
<Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
I don't give 5 stars freely and this particular store earned every one of them. In the course of roughly 13 months I made a major purchase from just about every department in the store as well as repair work from the Geek squad. I'm not exactly easy when it comes to trying to sell me something. Doesn't matter what it is I do my homework and I want what I want. I'm armed with tech data, accessories available, price differences between brands and models, when I hit the store. I usually have whatever it is I'm shopping for down to a couple of choices. I then go to the store to see them in person and then make my final decision. The great thing about Best Buy's sales people is they don't work off commission so they're not pushing the most expensive items at you. They are very knowledgeable about the items you're shopping for and can point out the model that will best service your needs not their paycheck. In those 13 months I purchased 4 flat panel TV's, a washer and dryer, a fridge, 2 home computers, and a home theater sound system. There may have been a stove on that list but I won't swear to it. I received the same assistance from a highly trained sales person on every purchase. No pressure, no rush, no problems. It probably took 5 hours or more to finally make up my mind over what surround sound to. The sales person was informative with the answers to all of my questions and deserves a medal for putting up with me for so long. In case you're wondering I went with the Bose and love it. Each department has similar stories but the same happy ending. 5 stars, absolutely!< /Text>

<Review>Returns - you will be lied to.

When attempting to return anything that's more than $100 that you purchased at another store or online, you will receive any number of lies about how they cannot do it in store.  "Too high value", "There's a lock on your order", "You didn't buy it here".

These are all incorrect statements (lies) - BestBuy as a corporation will take back anything that they sell, at any location, at any time.  The location has their own local financials to deal with, and if they push you to a different location or returning online, then it doesn't count against their balance books.

When returning something and are denied, just stand there and quote this review and make them prove their statements, with a request for the GMs card.  Your return will likely be processed.

A suggestion: Since it hurts your centers financials, clearly communicate that and offer customers that come in an expedited way to return online - have boxes and printers ready to ship out.  Many of us are happy to do something like that.  Don't bald-faced lie.  That's just bad form.<//Review>< rating>

<user>117777855496668243421< /user>< Text>
Returns - you will be lied to.

When attempting to return anything that's more than $100 that you purchased at another store or online, you will receive any number of lies about how they cannot do it in store.  "Too high value", "There's a lock on your order", "You didn't buy it here".

These are all incorrect statements (lies) - BestBuy as a corporation will take back anything that they sell, at any location, at any time.  The location has their own local financials to deal with, and if they push you to a different location or returning online, then it doesn't count against their balance books.

When returning something and are denied, just stand there and quote this review and make them prove their statements, with a request for the GMs card.  Your return will likely be processed.

A suggestion: Since it hurts your centers financials, clearly communicate that and offer customers that come in an expedited way to return online - have boxes and printers ready to ship out.  Many of us are happy to do something like that.  Don't bald-faced lie.  That's just bad form.< /Text>
